: 962}, {\"ngram\": \"performances\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 992}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A segment called \\\"Festivity\\\" - the eighth of 12 scenes celebrating aspects of French culture and history - paid tribute to French fashion with an inclusive runway show and party on a footbridge over the Seine, featuring drag queens and a transgender model.\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1283, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1105, \"end\": 1119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1150, \"end\": 1156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9996911083846699, \"rank\": 0.00016193606101696424, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1230, \"end\": 1235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.8689860957123907e-15, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A segment\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1036}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Festivity\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1054}, {\"ngram\": \"the eighth of 12 scenes\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1081}, {\"ngram\": \"aspects\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1101}, {\"ngram\": \"history - paid tribute\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"an inclusive runway show\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1194}, {\"ngram\": \"party\", \"from\": 1199, \"to\": 1204}, {\"ngram\": \"a footbridge\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1220}, {\"ngram\": \"drag queens\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1258}, {\"ngram\": \"a transgender model\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1282}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At one point in the sequence, several performers posed at the side of the runway, which doubled as a long dining table, in an artfully composed tableau that reminded some viewers of Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper,\\\" the Renaissance masterpiece depicting Jesus Christ and the apostles.\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1466, \"end\": 1483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2171405743615963e-38, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 1509, \"end\": 1520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renaissance\", \"score\": 0.9994425313555847, \"rank\": 0.0005577785508023384, \"text\": \"Renaissance\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renaissance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Renaissance\"}, {\"begin\": 1543, \"end\": 1555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.871570305885858e-13, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"one point\", \"from\": 1287, \"to\": 1296}, {\"ngram\": \"the sequence\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1312}, {\"ngram\": \"several performers\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1332}, {\"ngram\": \"the side\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1350}, {\"ngram\": \"the runway\", \"from\": 1354, \"to\": 1364}, {\"ngram\": \"a long dining table\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1402}, {\"ngram\": \"an artfully composed tableau\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1435}, {\"ngram\": \"some viewers\", \"from\": 1450, \"to\": 1462}, {\"ngram\": \"the apostles\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1572}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Later, in a portion of the sequence that did not air on NBC but was widely shared on social media, French entertainer Philippe Katerine appeared as Dionysus, the Greek god of wine-making, nearly naked, painted blue, and singing on a giant platter of fruit.\", \"from\": 1574, \"to\": 1831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1631, \"end\": 1634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.9999999997176019, \"rank\": 2.1991969033852722e-10, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}, {\"begin\": 1674, \"end\": 1680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9996911083846699, \"rank\": 0.00016193606101696424, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1693, \"end\": 1710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philippe Katerine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\"}, {\"begin\": 1723, \"end\": 1731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.353940901348608e-30, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 1737, \"end\": 1742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.9367696031656297, \"rank\": 0.06252857857640212, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a portion\", \"from\": 1584, \"to\": 1593}, {\"ngram\": \"the sequence\", \"from\": 1597